postcontent: Like its 5.56 mm counterpart, the MR762A1 is a direct descendent of the HK416/417 series, only in a semi-automatic rifle configuration developed for civilian users. Using the HK-proprietary operating system, the MR762A1 is gas operated and uses a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the common gas tube normally employed in AR15/M16/M4-style weapons. Pioneered by Heckler & Koch in the G36, HK416, and HK417; this method virtually eliminates malfunctions common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. The MR762A1 stays cleaner, reducing heat transfer to the bolt and bolt carrier, and drastically reducing wear and tear on other critical components. The service life of all parts is increased substantially. The MR762A1 uses a barrel produced by Heckler & Koch's famous cold hammer forging process. This manufacturing process uses the highest quality steel, producing a barrel that ensures superior accuracy, even after firing thousands of rounds. The MR762A1 is produced at Heckler & Koch's American manufacturing facilities from both American and German-made components.email (samson.2285@yahoo.com )

title: For Sale:  HK MR762 A1 308 Win / 7.62 NEW! H&K
postcontent: Like its 5.56 mm counterpart, the MR762A1 is a direct descendent of the HK416/417 series, only in a semi-automatic rifle configuration developed for civilian users. Using the HK-proprietary operating system, the MR762A1 is gas operated and uses a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the common gas tube normally employed in AR15/M16/M4-style weapons. Pioneered by Heckler & Koch in the G36, HK416, and HK417; this method virtually eliminates malfunctions common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. The MR762A1 stays cleaner, reducing heat transfer to the bolt and bolt carrier, and drastically reducing wear and tear on other critical components. The service life of all parts is increased substantially. The MR762A1 uses a barrel produced by Heckler & Koch's famous cold hammer forging process. This manufacturing process uses the highest quality steel, producing a barrel that ensures superior accuracy, even after firing thousands of rounds. The MR762A1 is produced at Heckler & Koch's American manufacturing facilities from both American and German-made components. email (samson.2285@yahoo.com )

title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig Sauer 556r (7.62x39) w/ many extras
postcontent:
Up for grabs is a gently used Gen 2 (not to be confused with the GEN 1) Sig Sauer 556r semi-automatic rifle. It is chambered in 7.62x39 (AK-47 round) and is very different from any other 556r you have probably ever seen before. 

This rifle was a custom build right from the start. At the factory, Sig added an optional aluminum quad-rail instead of the cheap looking plastic hand guard that typically comes on these rifles. I then went to work on it, adding various cosmetic/functional upgrades from top to bottom. Here is a list of everything that was added:

- Factory installed Aluminum quad rail ($299 upgrade option and worth every penny)
- Burris Fastfire III reflex red dot sight w/ Q.D. picatinny mount ($225) - currently zeroed at 50 yards.
- Single point sling adaptor and sling ($50)
- LWRC 'Rail Skin' rail protectors ($40)
- Front and Rear MagPul flip up B.U.Sights ($90) - Currently zeroed at 50 yards and perfectly co-witnessed with the Burris optic
- AIM Aluminum forward grip w/ Q3 Cree LED weapons light ($75) - 200 lumens if I remember right
- Additional 3 pack of rail protectors ($30)
- 10 total TAPCO 30 round magazines ($200) - all but 3 are brand new, unused
- BlackHawk Tactical soft carry case with ample room for magazines, slings, etc. 

*Also comes with the original box (including manual, lock, etc.), and a LIFETIME WARRANTY from Sig.

Overall, this rifle is used, but in excellent condition. I shot about 750 rounds through it and cleaned it after each use; it is barely broke in. Sig rates these rifles at around 40,000 rounds before servicing is recommended. It uses the extremely dependable gas piston system and has the Swiss style folding stock for tight spaces or other tactical situations. THIS IS THE FERRARI OF AK-47's. Clean lines, aggressive feel, and performs even better than it looks. 

I have nearly $2400 wrapped up in this package as it sits. I am giving it away at $1875. This is extremely fair for everything you are getting in this package. I cannot say enough how awesome this rifle is to shoot, own, and look at. 

To purchase, you must be 18 with a valid ID. FTF only, no shipping.

I also have approx. 2,000 rounds of Hollow Point and Soft Point 7.62x39 ammo - made by Wolf, most are the polymer coated kind for better performance. Non-corrosive and recent production. The buyer of the 556r package will get 1st option to buy this ammo and I will not sell it prior to the 556r being sold.

title: For Sale:  GEW-88 8mm bolt action rifle
postcontent:
This is a Gewehr 1888 commission rifle, chambered to shoot the 7.92x57 Mauser, otherwise known as the 8mm Mauser cartridge. It has a 5 shot magazine, loaded individually or by stripper clips. This particular rifle is one of those given to the Turkish forces during WWI, hence the Turkish markings on the top of the receiver. 

This rifle is clean and there does not appear to be any external importer markings visible. I have owned this rifle for over 30 years and it has sat in the safe. At some point before I purchased it, the stock was refinished. The barrel is pitted and dark, but the rifling is still sharp. 

Serial numbers are mostly matching, except for the trigger guard / magazine. It does have a cleaning rod, but no bayonet.

I am asking $250 or best offer. This is classified as an antique weapon. I also have some mil-surp 8mm ammo that I will throw in, some on stripper clips. I will not ship. Face to Face only and you will need to have ID please. I can arrange to meet you somewhere in the Reno area.

title: For Sale:  REAL Elcan SpecterDR 1-4x
postcontent:
As I've received a number of email responses to my previous posting for my authentic Elcan SpecterDR 1-4x optic claiming that it is a Chinese knock off, or that Elcan doesn't make a green Specter DR, I purchased one of the Chinese fakes and pictures of the two side-by-side.  In each of the pics, the real Elcan is shown above the fake one.

Raytheon Elcan did in fact produce a limited quantity of the SpecterDR in dark green and these were not sold to retail consumers but rather they were issued to certain elite units of the Canadian military.  To my knowledge these were the only recipients.  One very easy way to tell an authentic SpecterDR from a fake, aside from looking through the optic, is to look at the serial number.  Authentic Elcan SpecterDR optics will have this engraved on the unit and they do not have significant text on them whereas the fake units have a serial number painted on both sides and on the top and say Elcan SpecterDR on both sides.  Authentic Elcans also illuminate in two different ways while the knock off units only illuminate with a red dot.  The eye relief on authentic Elcan optics is another give-away as real ones will have an optimized optical path and will exhibit identical eye relief whether in 1x or 4x magnification.  As I know have both a real and knock-off Chinese made Elcan, I'm willing to sell either.

I hope this is helpful and thanks for looking.  The link below will direct you to one of many sites with posts discussing how to tell the difference between authentic and knock-off Elcan optics.  

http://thecounterfeitreport.com/product/292/Elcan-SpecterDR-Combat-Sight.html
From this post:
"The ELCAN SpecterDR Dual Role Optical Sight represents a revolution in optical sight design. The world's first truly dual field of view combat optical sight, the SpecterDR switches instantly from a 4x magnified sight to a 1x CQB sight with the throw of a lever. 
Unlike zoom sights, the SpecterDR offers an optimized optical path and identical eye relief in both 4x and 1x modes.
Elcan has reported counterfeit Elcan SpecterDR combat sights being sold on the internet. The counterfeit combat sights, while displaying counterfeit SpecterDR trademarked branding, are easy to identify when compared to the authentic combat sights.
All genuine Specter Sights by ELCAN are sold with; Unique serial numbers engraved on the body of the sight; Raytheon ELCAN branded (or authorized reseller) packaging; Raytheon ELCAN branded (or authorized reseller) User's Manual.
If the patented magnification switch lever is missing from a dual role sight -- it is counterfeit."
